    "problemStatement": "You are given a permutation PPP of NNN integers from 111 to NNN.\n\nThe weight of a subarray [L,R][L, R][L,R] (1\u2264L\u2264R\u2264N)(1\\le L \\le R \\le N)(1\u2264L\u2264R\u2264N) is defined as \u2223i\u2212j\u2223|i - j|\u2223i\u2212j\u2223 where iii denotes the index of the **maximum** element and jjj denotes the index of the **minimum** element in the subarray [L,R][L,R][L,R].\n\nFind the **sum** of the weights of **all** subarrays of the given permutation.\n\nNote that, \u2223X\u2223|X|\u2223X\u2223 denotes the absolute value of a number XXX. For example, \u2223\u22124\u2223=4|-4| = 4\u2223\u22124\u2223=4 and \u22237\u2223=7|7| = 7\u22237\u2223=7.\n\n\nInput Format\n\nThe first line contains an integer TTT, denoting the number of test cases. The TTT test cases then follow:\nThe first line of each test case contains an integer NNN, denoting the length of the permutation.\nThe second line of each test case contains NNN space-separated integers P1,P2,\u2026,PNP_1,P_2,\\ldots,P_NP1\u200b,P2\u200b,\u2026,PN\u200b, denoting the elements of the permutation.\n\n\nOutput Format\nFor each test case, output the **sum** of the weights of all subarrays of the given permutation.",
    "constraints": [
      "1\u2264T\u22641051 \\leq T \\leq 10^51\u2264T\u2264105",
      "1\u2264N\u22645\u22c51051 \\leq N \\leq 5\\cdot 10^51\u2264N\u22645\u22c5105",
      "1\u2264Pi\u2264N1 \\leq P_i \\leq N1\u2264Pi\u200b\u2264N and Pi\u2260PjP_i \\neq P_jPi\u200b\ue020=Pj\u200b for i\u2260ji \\neq ji\ue020=j",
      "Sum of NNN over all test cases does not exceed 5\u22c51055\\cdot 10^55\u22c5105."
    ],
