        "explanation": "Explanation:\nTest case 111:\n\nThe weights of the subarrays [1,1],[2,2],[3,3][1,1],[2,2],[3,3][1,1],[2,2],[3,3] are 000 as i=ji=ji=j in all these subarrays.\nSubarray [L,R]=[1,2][L,R] = [1,2][L,R]=[1,2] has weight 111 as i=1i=1i=1 and j=2j=2j=2: \u22231\u22122\u2223=1|1 - 2| =1\u22231\u22122\u2223=1.\nSubarray [L,R]=[2,3][L,R] = [2,3][L,R]=[2,3] has weight 111 as i=2i=2i=2 and j=3j=3j=3: \u22232\u22123\u2223=1|2 - 3| =1\u22232\u22123\u2223=1.\nSubarray [L,R]=[1,3][L,R] = [1,3][L,R]=[1,3] has weight 222 as i=1i=1i=1 and j=3j=3j=3: \u22231\u22123\u2223=2|1 - 3| =2\u22231\u22123\u2223=2.\n\nSum of weights is 1+1+2=41+1+2=41+1+2=4.\nTest case 222:\n\nThe weights of the subarrays [1,1],[2,2],[3,3],[4,4][1,1],[2,2],[3,3],[4,4][1,1],[2,2],[3,3],[4,4] are 000 as i=ji = ji=j in all these subarrays.\nSubarray [L,R]=[1,2][L,R] = [1,2][L,R]=[1,2] has weight 111 as i=2i=2i=2 and j=1j=1j=1: \u22232\u22121\u2223=1|2 - 1| =1\u22232\u22121\u2223=1.\nSubarray [L,R]=[2,3][L,R] = [2,3][L,R]=[2,3] has weight 111 as i=2i=2i=2 and j=3j=3j=3: \u22232\u22123\u2223=1|2 - 3| =1\u22232\u22123\u2223=1.\nSubarray [L,R]=[3,4][L,R] = [3,4][L,R]=[3,4] has weight 111 as i=3i=3i=3 and j=4j=4j=4: \u22233\u22124\u2223=1|3 - 4| =1\u22233\u22124\u2223=1.\nSubarray [L,R]=[1,3][L,R] = [1,3][L,R]=[1,3] has weight 111 as i=2i=2i=2 and j=1j=1j=1: \u22232\u22121\u2223=1|2 - 1| =1\u22232\u22121\u2223=1.\nSubarray [L,R]=[2,4][L,R] = [2,4][L,R]=[2,4] has weight 222 as i=2i=2i=2 and j=4j=4j=4: \u22232\u22124\u2223=2|2 - 4| =2\u22232\u22124\u2223=2.\nSubarray [L,R]=[1,4][L,R] = [1,4][L,R]=[1,4] has weight 111 as i=2i=2i=2 and j=1j=1j=1: \u22232\u22121\u2223=1|2 - 1| =1\u22232\u22121\u2223=1.\n\nSum of weights is 1+1+1+1+2+1=71+1+1+1+2+1=71+1+1+1+2+1=7."
      }
